wikipedia_page.main: Henrietta Wilfrida "Frida" Leakey born Henrietta Avern, aka H. Wilfrida Leakey (1902 – 19 August 1993) was a British teacher who discovered a gorge that was named FLK or "Frida Leakey Korongo". The gorge was the site of ancient stone tools and important human fossil discoveries. Leakey was the first wife of Louis Leakey. She became a leader in the Women's Institute and a County Councillor.
